Resource Center
Welcome to the one-stop center for all your document needs. You can open any folder or document simply by clicking on the item. When you reach the document of interest, you can download it to your computer, print it, or view it on-line.

Need Help? Enter one or more keywords and select Search - we'll search the entire archives for you.

Board Room
Visit the Board Room for information about your Board: Directors, Meeting Agendas, and more.  The Resident Directors are elected by the homeowners, or as otherwise specified in the Bylaws. For further information about the limitation and restrictions of the powers of the Board of Directors, please refer to the Governing Documents.  You're welcome to attend any Board meeting, just be sure to check the on-line Calendar for date, time, and location.

March 2023 meeting minutes
WOMEN OF WOODBRIDGE
Minutes of Monthly Meeting
March 15, 2023
 
 
Meeting started at 11:05 with 31 members present.
 
A NEW MEMBER, Kathy Hall was introduced and welcomed by all.
 
The minutes from the February meeting were read and approved.
 
TREASURER�S REPORT
(Interim report as the bank statement closes on March 17th)
 
? Manteca EVERY 15 MINUTES Donation $1,700.00
(Proceeds from October 2022 event)
 
? Deposit from Texas Roadhouse March 2023 $3,885.00
( as of March 13,2023)
 
? OVERVIEW  Bank Balance                                                                        $2,059.61
              Upcoming expenditures from General fund                                              
                MEET & GREET in June                                                          ($600.00)
 
? BANK BALANCE                                                                                                $1,459.60
 
Polly Smith gave an update on the SIP event scheduled for May 4th.  The theme is �A DAY AT THE RACES.�

Tickets are on sale NOW at the front desk.  More volunteers are needed especially for the clean up committee.
 
Sandi Kinyon and Doreen Nunes are working on the baskets to be auctioned.  They too could use more volunteers both in collecting donation items and gift  cards.  All items DUE APRIL 15TH  to Doreen Nunes.

With 20 baskets on display in the living room and another 20 on the patio, others are needed to help with the action that evening.

Guest speaker, Steve Schluer gave us a great introduction to the EVERY 15 MINUTE program.  He shared how the program came to be and how it is presented today.  This program reaches out to ALL Manteca students to give a visual of how the influence of ANY drug or alcohol can affect the lives of so many.

Chairpersons were still needed for the MEET & GREET in June.  Penny Tenczar and Janet Cameron have volunteered.

The Hope Shelter request to sponsor a room has been table for future review.
 
GLITZ & GLAMOUR is a semi-formal event scheduled for the last Saturday in September this year.
Birdie Neiri and Linda Pace are planning a �Dinner by the Lake� with dancing.
 
The next meeting is April 19th at 11:00 a.m.
Meeting adjourned at 11:50

                             Monthly Meeting Minutes
                                      February 15, 2023

February meeting started at 11:00 a.m. with 34 members present.  Two New Members were welcomed, Brenda Junginger and Joan Alvarez.
First order of business ,President Sharon Naramore thanked all of the committee members and attendees that made the Luncheon the success it was after two year hiatus.
Members approved minutes from the January meeting and the Treasurer's Report accepted.

- TREASURERS' REPORT
     Current balance   $8,831.82
Deposits:    $50.00               Refund HOA

                      $2,000  Scholarships for 2023 to Discovery Challenge
                    $2,750   Luncheon Sponsorships
OLD BUSINESS 
 Follow up on the lucheon and silent auction - both a huge success.
Every 15  minutes -  Kathy Howe updated on the Texas Roadhouse dinner March 27th.  Kathy aalso explained the Every 15 Minutes program and Police and Fire will have a representative at the March meeting.
SIP event - Polly Smith and Sue Edmiston co-chairs for May 4th.  As chairs of the Auction committee, Doreen Nunes and Sandi Kinyon are in need of volunteers to help contacting donors for the event.  They have sign up lists and lists of those who have donated in the past for reference.
They are still in search of a theme  and Nancy Blakeman has joined the team.
Fall event in the planning and scheduled for September 30th.

Next meeting March 15, 2023 11 a.m.
Guest speaker from MUSD's  "Every 15 Minutes." 

Adjourned :   11:45
Submitted by Cathy Stanley, Secretary

 Women of Woodbridge (WOW) 
Monthly Meeting Minutes 
January 18, 2023 

Meeting started promptly at 11 A.M. with 64 women present. 
INTRODUCTIONS: Jacque Foster (Vice-President) opened the meeting with the introduction of the new President Sharon Naramore and the re-introduction of the Secretary, Cathy Stanley and the Treasurer, Lee Croletto. 
NEW MEMBERS: Three new members were welcomed, Marianne Smith, Kathy Wright and Norma Patrick. 
Members approved the Minutes of the November meeting and accepted the Treasurer�s report. 
Treasurers Report from January 18, 2023 was shared by Sue Edminston. 
Current Balance $8,831.82 
Activity this Month: 
Deposits: $ 50.00 Refund from HOA 
$ 6.05 Change from Adopt A Family 
$ 3,300.00 Cash for Adopt a Family 
Checks: $ 680.00 BE. Cuisine for Scones (Shop with a Cop) 
$ 1,000.00 Police Chief�s Foundation (Shop with a 
Cop) 
Profit on Fundraiser: $ 762.40 Shop with a Cop 
NEW BUSINESS: Hearts and Flowers Luncheon. Mary Anne Abercrombie and Polly Smith, Chair-Persons. 
The Luncheon will be one day this year, Saturday February 11, 2023. 
Hostess, decoration and food committees all reported they are under control. Tickets were sold at the meeting and the following day hoping for a sell-out. You may contact Marianne with any further questions regarding tickets. 
Silent Auction �Nancy Galanida andStephanie Telles have been working on this. Items will be on display February 6th through the 11th . 
UP COMING EVENTS: SIP event is May 4th, 2023. We need members to Chair/Co-Chair and volunteers for all committees. 
Sandy Kinyon has a binder to help give direction for a successful event. There is a lot of preparation to be planned in advance. The Silent Auction will be handled by Sandy Kinyon and Doreen Nunes they will need to start work as early as March to gather items and preparation for the ticket sales in April. 
MEET AND GREET: will be June 14th. Again welcoming all who can help make the evening a success. 
There was discussion to have the Drive Thru Dinner Event again. 
Looking to have an event in October this year. Any thoughts and ideas are welcome. 
Meeting Adjourned at 12:15 P.M. 
****Next meeting is February 15th at 11:00 AM

City Permits
This folder contains a compilation of Manteca City Permits that are useful to residents.
Alarm Permit

If you have a monitored alarm system in your home, you have between January 1st-31st to register with the city. In order to make alarm permits easier to process and regulate the PD has an annual application period from January 1-31. If someone had an alarm system installed in July and applied for an alarm permit (in July), they would need to do it again in January and every January after that to stay in compliance.

http://www.ci.manteca.ca.us/Finance/OnLine%20Forms/Alarm%20Permit.pdf


 

 

 

To download the Adobe Acrobat reader, click here.
View On-line Download Print
Temporary Permit for Camping & Oversized Vehicle Parking
Unless you are loading, unloading, cleaning or doing a quick repair, you are not allowed to park your RV on a residential street, Monday-Friday, except major holiday. If you are going to have your RV parked on the street for longer than that, you can apply for and get (for free) a parking permit that will allow you to park your RV in front of your home for 5-consecutive days (but no more than 10-days in a 90 day period). To obtain a a permit (it is almost immediately approved), just go down to the police department.

Communications Committee
The purpose of the Communications Committee is to conduct work to provide for organization of documents, document change control procedures and policies, and improvement of user experiences on the �community portal�. Improvement of this portal shall include understanding and setting up any customizable layout, organization of contents, development of full functionality. The work will be consistent with the Policy for Retention, format, and retrieval of electronic media.
